# Molding #157 Small issue – EAP system can not turn on

## Issue
- Issue: EAP system can not turn on
- Model: Attis
- Machine: EQMLD00157
- Time: 22:00 23/02/2026

## Symptom
- EAP system could not be turned on.
- Machine could not connect with EAP system.
- HMI abnormal condition showed SecsGem On/Off function hidden.

## Root Cause
- Normally the button “Turn on/off” for SecsGem function appears automatically on HMI of molding machine.
- Because the machine stayed turned off for a long time, the IP address of the machine changed.
- After IP address changed, the On/Off SecsGem function became hidden.
- Because the SecsGem function was hidden, the molding machine could not connect with EAP system.

## Failure Mechanism
- EAP communication depends on the SecsGem function being available and correctly mapped on the machine HMI.
- After long machine-off duration, machine IP address changed from the expected network setting.
- Because the communication condition no longer matched the expected IP / RMS environment, the SecsGem on/off function was hidden on HMI.
- Once SecsGem was not available, the machine could not establish connection with EAP system.

## Actions
1. Temporary run by software Laser 2D
   - Status: Done

2. SMD team support debug RMS system following the new IP address
   - Checkpoint: 24/2

3. IT team support to fix IP address of molding machine
   - Checkpoint: 24/2

## Current Status
- Temporary production workaround by software Laser 2D was completed.
- Root cause direction points to communication / IP-address mismatch affecting SecsGem/EAP turn-on condition.
